What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A boatload of reading and writing. An interesting class (and even better if you have good classmates). Thought provoking topics. Especially relevant if you are an athlete/ minority/ woman or any combination o the three. I also thing guys can benefit a lot from this class.

Expect a heavy workload. Definitely my most challenging and frustrating class this semester, but I definitely became a better writer from taking it. The topics of in-class discussion were always interesting.
If you love sports, I WOULD DEFINITELY TAKE THIS CLASS! It is a lot of work though: readings, reading responses, four papers with drafts.
It offers a really interesting and different way to look at sports. You also develop critical reading skills and a good foundation for writing essays.
Yes, I would recommend the course but be ready for a lot of work
I would recommend the class based on the subject, not for improving writing. Sports lovers should take this for a writing credit, but probably not anyone else.
